 :teraflop club: /te'r*-flop kluhb/ /n./ [FLOP = Floating Point Operation] A
mythical association of people who consume outrageous amounts of computer
time in order to produce a few simple pictures of glass balls with intricate
ray-tracing techniques. Caltech professor James Kajiya is said to have been
the founder. Compare {Knights of the Lambda Calculus}.